<?xml version="1.0"?>


<RDF xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:em="http://www.mozilla.org/2004/em-rdf#">

<Description about="urn:mozilla:install-manifest">
    <em:id>sendtocategory@jobisoft.de</em:id>
    <em:version>1.58</em:version>
    <em:type>2</em:type>
    
    <!-- Target Application this theme can install into, 
        with minimum and maximum supported versions. --> 
    <em:targetApplication>
      <Description>
        <!-- Thunderbird -->
        <em:id>{3550f703-e582-4d05-9a08-453d09bdfdc6}</em:id> 
        <em:minVersion>3.1a1pre</em:minVersion>
        <em:maxVersion>28.0</em:maxVersion>
      </Description>
    </em:targetApplication>


    <!-- Front End MetaData -->
    <em:name>CategoryManager</em:name>
    <em:description>If you use one ore more external CardDav addressbooks (hooked into Thunderbird via the SOGo-Connector), Thunderbird has access to the category field of each CardDav contact.

This Add-On provides some category management functions and allows sending an email to all members of a category. It has been developed, to overcome the limitations of the Thunderbird lists, which do not sync very well via CardDav, and have problems if a contact is part of more than one list. 

This Add-On only works with CardDav addressbooks and needs the SOGo-Connector to be installed. If an ownCloud server or a Baikal server is used as CardDav server instead of a SOGo server, users have reported, that SOGo-Connector 10.0.6 needs to be used.
</em:description>
    <em:creator>John Bieling</em:creator>

  </Description>      

</RDF>
